name: microservices-with-NATs
description: This architecture employs an API Gateway as the central entry point for client requests, which are then routed to various microservices using NATS for asynchronous and decoupled communication. The system consists of three main microservices: User, Payment, and Notification services, all interacting through NATS.

name: store-stock-management
description: The Store Stock Management API is a backend system for managing store inventory, requisitions, purchase orders, gate passes, documents, and store management. This project uses Node.js, Express.js, PostgreSQL with Sequelize ORM, Swagger for API documentation, and Winston for logging. The architecture follows a microservices approach.
